## Advanced Vehicle Testing: Wheel Force Transducer Data Collection

As part of SRB-25 vehicle testing, the electronics team supported a data collection event using a wheel force transducer loaned by Michigan Scientific. The goal of the test was to collect real-world wheel load data during Baja SAE vehicle operation and provide useful information for future suspension, chassis, and vehicle dynamics analysis.

This testing event expanded the vehicle electronics and data acquisition effort beyond standard onboard sensors and introduced professional-grade instrumentation into the team's validation process.

### Test Objectives

- Collect real-world wheel force data during vehicle operation
- Support suspension and chassis performance evaluation
- Validate the vehicle electronics and data acquisition workflow during live testing
- Provide measured data that can be reviewed by suspension, chassis, and vehicle dynamics teams
- Improve future design decisions using test-based feedback

### Instrumentation

- Michigan Scientific Wheel Force Transducer
- Baja SAE vehicle electronics system
- Data acquisition hardware
- On-vehicle wiring and sensor infrastructure

### My Role

As Electronics Lead, I supported the vehicle electronics readiness and data collection effort for the wheel force transducer testing event. This included helping ensure the vehicle electrical system, wiring, and data acquisition setup were prepared for testing.

### Current Status

Wheel force transducer data was collected during the testing event. Detailed post-processing and analysis are still in progress.

Planned analysis includes:

- Wheel load trends during vehicle operation
- Suspension loading behavior
- Chassis loading observations
- Correlation with onboard vehicle sensor data
- Design feedback for future Baja SAE suspension and chassis development

### Engineering Value

This testing event showed the importance of validating vehicle design decisions with measured real-world data. The wheel force transducer test provided hands-on exposure to advanced vehicle instrumentation, experimental testing, and data acquisition methods commonly used in automotive and motorsports engineering.

